History of DevOps

DevOps is a new concept in software development.
Patrick Debois organised the first DevOpsDays conference in Ghent, belgium in 2008.
In 2009, Jon Allspaw and Paul Hammond gave atalk at the Velocu=ity Confernece
The Term "DevOps: itself is believed to have been coined by Andrew Clay Shafer and Patrick Debois
There are also other thought leaders such ass Gene Kim, Jez Humble, and Nicole Forsgren
DevOps is seen as a key enabler of digital transformation.
